structured.description: A constant function named "fn" that returns no value and logs the number 0 to the console using the console.log() method from the browser's built-in console API. The fn is a function expression defined as an arrow function.

items.description: Defines a constant arrow function that logs "0" to the console when invoked. The function does not accept any arguments and simply outputs the value 0 when called.
items.name: fn
